The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, January 16, 2004 				 Insult apology
																								New Delhi, Jan. 15: The Congress today sought an apology from the BJP for its uncivilised remarks against party president Sonia Gandhi, reports our special correspondent.																								The party threatened to tear apart the image of Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee if an apology was not tendered.																								The Congress said it would resort to democratic options to counter the offensive. The party said Vajpayee has perfected double-speak into an art.
